## Authentication contract

The SPA talks to `django-allauth`'s **headless** API at `/_allauth/browser/v1/...`. See `apps/users/middleware.py` for backend MFA enforcement.

Login flow:

```
POST /_allauth/browser/v1/auth/login                  { email, password }
  200 → user is signed in ({ data.user })
  401 + flows[].id === "mfa_authenticate" → MFA challenge view
  401 + flows[].id === "verify_email" → "check your email" view
  401 (no flows) → invalid credentials
  429 → cool-down message
```

The auth store (`stores/auth.ts`) returns an exhaustive Result type so the caller can't accidentally drop a branch.

### Why session cookies and not JWTs?

Storing tokens in `localStorage` is an OWASP A02 anti-pattern — XSS becomes total account takeover. With Django's session cookies:
- `sessionid` is `HttpOnly` — XSS cannot read it.
- `SameSite=Lax` blocks cross-site cookie forwarding.
- The CSRF token is the only cookie JS reads, and it's only useful in a same-site context.

If you NEED a JWT (mobile, IoT), use [`django-ninja-jwt`](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/#django-ninja-jwt) or [SimpleJWT](https://django-rest-framework-simplejwt.readthedocs.io/) at a separate `/api/token/*` namespace — never mix the two on the same route.

## Theming

Tailwind v4 is configured CSS-first in `src/assets/css/main.css` via `@theme`. Brand tokens live there — adjust `--color-brand-*` to your palette. Dark mode via `useColorMode()` composable; toggle in the default layout flips between light/dark and persists to `localStorage`.

## Security baseline (what's already on)

- Every fetch uses `credentials: "include"` — required for session cookies.
- Every mutating fetch sends `X-CSRFToken` via `csrfHeaders()`.
- Strict CSP `connect-src` already includes the Vue dev origin (`config/settings/base.py`).
- `vue/no-v-html` ESLint rule bans raw-HTML injection sinks.
- Source maps disabled in production builds.
- Sentry SDK (when `use_sentry=true`) auto-installed; configure `VITE_SENTRY_DSN`.

## Bundle-size budget

`vite.config.ts` warns at 250 KB per chunk. Vue + Vue Router + Pinia + Tailwind land at ~140 KB on a clean build — plenty of room for project code.

